# One Card Limit Poker

A Python implementation of One Card Limit Poker, featuring both human and AI players.

## Features
- Configurable deck size (3-13 cards)
- Adjustable maximum raises (0-2)
- Human vs Computer gameplay
- CLI interface
- Built-in strategy framework
- Game state logging

## Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/one_card_limit.git
cd one_card_limit

# Install in development mode
pip install -e .
```

## Quick Start

```python
from one_card_limit.interface.game_manager import GameManager
from one_card_limit.core.state import GameConfig

# Create game with custom configuration
config = GameConfig(deck_size=3, max_raises=2, ante=1)
game = GameManager(initial_stack=100, config=config)

# Play 10 hands
game.play_session(10)
```

## Game Rules
1. Each player is dealt one card
2. Players take turns betting, raising, or folding
3. Maximum of 2 raises per betting round
4. Higher card wins at showdown

